pet.name: Foster Dog Blog
pet.description:
Here’s your chance to get to know some of the dogs that are not ready for adoption yet but are currently in foster care. Enjoy their stories.

www.BrooklineLabRescue.org/blog

If you are interested in adopting a Lab from our Rescue, please visit our Web site, www.brooklinelabrescue.org, for more information on our adoption process. If you need additional information about the adoption process or whether you are in our coverage area, please send an e-mail to our Rescue at info@brooklinelabrescue.org

Even if you are not ready to adopt, you can still help us help our Labs!

Brookline Labrador Retriever Rescue is a 501(c)3 non-profit volunteer organization funded entirely by donations. Donations are always needed to help with veterinary costs, transportation, and supplies for our dogs. For information on donating to BLRR please click here. Donations are accepted via PayPal or you can mail a check to: Brookline Labrador Retriever Rescue, P.O. Box 638, Warrington, PA 18976-0638

pet.name: Sable
pet.breed: Labrador Retriever / American Staffordshire Terrier / Mixed
pet.description:
Come visit me this Sat/Sun October 10th & 11th, Pet Smart, El Segundo Plaza, 730 S. Sepulveda Blvd. El Segundo, 90245 12-4:30 Woof !!



Talk about survival . . . Sable wins the prize for most Spunk !

While at the Shelter to rescue Roy (also on Petfinder) we met Sable who was Roy's kennel mate. While taking Roy out of his cage for adoption, Sable took advantage of the small opening and 'literally' jumped in to my arms - full body leap ! I asked the Animal Control Officer about this precocious pup and sadly learned that she was to be euthanized in 2 days as they were at capacity. Still in my arms, I looked in Sable's eyes, back to the caring Animal Control Officer - both of them pleading silently - and even though we had no place to board her, Sable became part of our rescue group ! How could we resist such a plea. At just 3 years old, this precious Pointing Lab and Am Staff mix is about as nice as they come. With a beautiful 'seal' colored coat, Sable is truly a beautiful girl. Sable loves other dogs, loves to go to the dog park and is attracted to all black pooches, but 'everyone' is her friend. Oddly, English Bulldogs appear to be smitten with Sable ! Sable is in a loving foster home with a loving and intelligent companion, Perry. Perry is teaching Sable how to be a 'proper' lady, but can't quite get the coquette out of the girl ! While 14 months, Sable is still the puppy and soaks up training like a sponge - full of puppy mischief - all is forgiven when Sable gives you her tummy and looks you in the eyes.
See Sable Live on Good Day LA :
http://www.myfoxla.com/myfox/pages/InsideFox/Detail?contentId=1900047&version=2&locale=EN-US&layoutCode=VSTY&pageId=5.2.1

If you are interested in meeting this dog, please call Elizabeth at 310-995-1221 or email her at pitstoprescue@ca.rr.com. ADOPTION REQUIREMENTS: Application, Contract, Home-Check and Tax-deductible adoption fee/donation. All animals are healthy, altered, micro-chipped and up-to-date on all shots.

pet.name: Nikki
pet.description:
The vet couldn't believe we got Nikki from a pound ! This absolutely gorgeous and stunning girl was dumped at the pound because she and her Mastiff sibling got into a fight - A shelter favorite, they were determined to give Nikki a 2nd chance with the help of a qualified rescue. The minute we saw Nikki, we agreed to take her. Only 3 years old, Nikki has been part of the MPSR group since November 2007. Nikki now shares her home with a Poodle, another Pit Bull, a Chihuahua & a Pekinese. Still unskilled at dog etiquette and too protective to allow her to be part of a multi dog home, we prefer to call Nikki 'Dog Intolerant' - and are looking for a home where she will be your one and only. Nikki is super affectionate, intelligent, athletic and can jump a 5 foot wall as if she is floating. Nikki loves her walks, car rides, but most of all shadowing you around the house striking a pose !

If you are interested in meeting this dog, please call Elizabeth at 310-995-1221 or email her at pitstoprescue@ca.rr.com. ADOPTION REQUIREMENTS: Application, Contract, Home-Check and Tax-deductible adoption fee/donation. All animals are healthy, altered, micro-chipped and up-to-date on all shots.

pet.name: Willow
pet.description: Just a regular, little, brown Chihuahua . . . As comforting as that old pair of slippers one refuses to part with, the snuggly sweater from a few seasons passed – this little girl will make you think of times when things were a bit more simple, life less complicated.  Miss Willow touched our hearts when we heard from one of our volunteers of a little Mommy that had 3 wee ones and who was being abused by her current Guardian.  Thankfully, the pups weren’t with the man long enough to have endured what Willow did and stayed true to the sweet nature Mommy passed on genetically.  Willow is in a foster home where she plays with other dogs, goes for long power walks, cuddles on the sofa in her very special bed and now never knows a harsh word or action.  Willow is quickly adapting to the world as a kind place and is very bonded to Foster Mom who has shown her only kindness while also bolstering her confidence.  Willow learned that the best defense is a good offense, but after just a few weeks, now looks to foster Mom to watch her back.  Willow is about 5 years old, 9 pounds, in good physical shape and now is ready to find her dream home.  Willow is an intelligent, loving and beautiful little spirit who is truly the epitome of a *rescue* pup grateful for the smallest act of kindness with a heart as big as her ability to forgive.

pet.name: Chloe
pet.description:
Chloe came from a high kill shelter with just week old pups. A few days later Chloe was diagnosed with Parvo and needed fluids and meds right away. Immediatly her pups were taken from her so that she may get better. Chloe is all better now and is now spayed. She is a really sweet girl who loves to cuddle and sleep in bed with you. She is also crate trained but prefers the people bed. She is good with kids and other dogs too! Learning to walk on a leash...still just a bit nervous about that. 

***was spayed on 3/17

Shots up to date wormed with Nemex, frontline applied, micro chipping is available at no additional charge

Adoption cost for this dog is $100

We are a rescue, and do not have a physical shelter to visit. All of our dogs/pups are currently being fostered in the Central Valley so please be willing to make the trip to see them if you are from out of the area. Our adoption process REQUIRES that an application must first be submitted and approved prior to meeting any of our pets.

Just note that we may get several responses on one pet at a time so just because you have an approved application does not mean said pet is on hold for you. One must FIRST confirm an appointment to meet the pet after an approved application has been sent.

To inquire about this specific pet, please write to pupznpalz@yahoo.com for an application. Please remember to put the pets name in the subject line when emailing, and on the top on the application. It helps us to help you that must faster. We are a group of volunteers, and ask that you please bare with us. We will get to each person just as quickly as we can.

If you do not hear back from us within 24 hours, please send another request as we have been having problems with e-mail. Or feel free to contact Karri at 209-480-8662 between normal business hours of 9-6.

Please note: The email address pupznpalz@aol.com is no nonger active. Please do NOT send any email there as we will not receive it. The blog is also no longer active...please email for an application..do not go to the blog.

pet.name: AA-Sam
pet.description:
Please contact Tonya Griffith (TMSGriffith@aol.com) for more information about this pet.

Pictures updated 6/9/09 and transferred to us 6/22/09.  He was being crated at night and when I ran errands, and did very well, so house training should be easy.  He followed me wherever I would go, does well on a leash, and his fur is Reddish Brown.  I later put him in a dog pen due to him following me too closely all the time while trying to do my chores.

D.O.B.:     ? August 2008
Weight:     42.7 - 7/3/09

$75 adoption fee will pay for his neuter and vaccinations.

Posted 5/20/09 for Kahne Parsons Walker.  'I live out here at Lake Hawkins.  We get a lot of stray animals dumped out here and there are practically no resources for dealing with the unfortunate animals.  Recently someone dumped (or so I believe) a dog near our house.  I did not aim to take him in, but he found his way into our yard, burrowing under our gates, and so like it or not he is here.  I called the East Texas shelter and they are not currently taking in dogs. So, until I can find a situation, I will have to see that he comes to no harm.  He is currently at the vet's getting wormed and receiving his shots.  I don't know his breed or exactly how old he is.  Dr. Hobbs thinks he may have some Australian shepherd in him by the look of his ears.  He is very friendly and gets along with other dogs (even our male dog, who is very territorial).  He is not yet neutered.  He has lots of puppy energy, but seems bright and trainable.

We really can't keep him for long.  We already have two dogs and four cats, all of them former strays.  You know how much it costs to properly care for animals and as my husband and I are both school teachers we don't have a lot of extra cash.

He weighs 35 pounds and is about 9 months old (acc. to the vet).  He has had his first shots and been wormed, has tested negative for heartworms and begun
preventative treatment, and is also on Frontline.  He was not neutered when found.  He is as tall/long as his adult growth though he will likely fill out more.  We do not know the mix of breeds that produced him, but he is lean and fast and can JUMP.  (Someone who wants a dog who can catch frisbees or jump through hoops would
love him.)

I have taught him to fetch, and he does, in his own fashion.  He still has a lot of energy, and that makes it hard to instill discipline, but I'll do what I can.'

pet.name: TG-Lex
pet.description:
Please contact Tonya Griffith (TMSGriffith@aol.com) for more information about this pet.

Gary lost his job of 7 years when the economy went bad, and has not been able to find another permanent job yet.  Gary received an eviction notice 2/10/11, and all the cats and 2 dogs at his house were surrendered to us to find new homes.

Posted 4/5/11, and pictures taken 3/6/11.  Lex is very sweet, but can be skittish of new people.  He use to be afraid to come near me, but in a short time has become very loveable with me.  Lex and his sibling were puppies at a Wal-Mart parking lot when Gary and Penny took them.  The owners couldn't find a home for them, and were just going to leave them in the parking lot.

D.O.B.:     ? 2003 or 2004
Weight:     about 50 pounds

$80.00 adoption fee will pay for his neuter and vaccinations.  We cannot do his neuter at this time due to him having heartworms.  He was never given heartworm prevention until he came here.  He is too hyper to give the heartworm treatment to, so we are keeping him on prevention for awhile in hopes he can be neutered later on.  If he were to be sedated for surgery, it could kill him.

pet.name: TG-Maddie
pet.description:
Please contact Tonya Griffith (TMSGriffith@aol.com) for more information about this pet.

Maddie was a stray found in Bullard, Texas.  She was untrusting and scared of new people at first, but now she is a great guard dog if I'm not around, even though she is a hound.  She doesn't want to be in a dog pen, doesn't really want to ride in a vehicle, but wants to follow as if she doesn't want to be abandoned.  She gets very excited when we come home, wrinkling her nose, and her hound bark is sweet.  Maddie has been with us since April 2004.  We had to eventually put her on a 20 foot lightweight chain, since she has gotten out of our perimeter fence several times, and will lay on the road, even with vehicles driving by, and won't let us come near her when she is on the road.  She is also very intelligent.  She won't get in a live trap or crate anymore, knowing that's how we caught her before, so if she gets out anymore, the only thing that will bring her back through the gate is a storm.  We don't have a dog pen strong enough to keep her in yet, so she is right outside our front door, which gives her more social interaction with us as we go in and out.  The last few times she has gotten off her chain, she has stayed on the property, so having more interaction with us each day has made a difference.  She has a large fancy wooden dog house that was donated, and we fill it with cedar shavings for her to sleep in.

March 2005, I had leashed her for a few walks, and it is as if she has been leash trained before. She would walk directly beside me on the left side.

D.O.B.:     ? 2002
Weight:      about 50 pounds

$60 adoption fee will pay for her spay and vaccinations.

pet.name: TG-Nathan
pet.description:
Please contact Tonya Griffith (TMSGriffith@aol.com) for more information about this pet.

Nathan was a stray found in February 2007.  He had several patches of skin missing, which turned out to be demodectic mange, but has all of his hair back and kept it by using Nu Stock, and keeping him on Ivomec for heartworm prevention.  He was skittish of people at first, and was starving, but now he is a very sweet dog looking for a loving home.  He has put on a lot of weight after he was neutered, which can happen to some pets, but we are not set up to isolate the dogs for special diets, so he could really use a good home of his own.

D.O.B.:     ? 2005
Weight:     68.0 - 3/15/07

$65 adoption fee will pay for his neuter and vaccinations.

pet.name: TG-Precious
pet.breed: Catahoula Leopard Dog / Pit Bull Terrier / Mixed &#40;short coat&#41;
pet.description:
Please contact Tonya Griffith (TMSGriffith@aol.com) for more information about this pet.

Precious was surrendered May 20, 2007.  I was told she had been seen getting beat by her owners, and I was also told she had been shot at by someone.  The bullet grazed the back of her shoulder blades.  The hair did grow back in where I was told she had been shot.

She is a climber, is leash trained, and crate trained, but I have to let her hike her leg on something outside before bringing her in to a crate, or she will do it inside the store room where the crates are.  Yes, I said hike, just like a male dog.  I don't know why.  She is paired up with Marshall, and he has the same problem, so maybe it's from being with him.  She didn't use to be like that until I paired her up with Marshall, so she could be trained again.  She use to be a yard dog that was crated at night and when I ran errands, but kept climbing over our four foot perimeter fence and bothering the neighbor, so she had to go in a six foot dog pen she couldn't get out of.  I still have to crate her when I run errands, or she starts working on the chain link fence or digging to get out, so she is still crated when I leave, but not at night.  She has become extremely sweet and more social now since she has been here.  She use to be scared of most movements we made, but is now comfortable.  I don't even need a leash with her.  On occasion I will have her out of her dog pen when the other yard dogs are crated, and she will follow me wherever I go, and comes quickly anytime I call her.  If I sit down, she is in my lap wanting to be pet, and will even roll over for a belly rub.  She would make a great personal pet for someone, and is good around children.

D.O.B.:     ? 2005
Weight:      53.7 - 5/23/07

$70 adoption fee will pay for her spay and vaccinations.

pet.name: TG-Reba
pet.description:
Please contact Tonya Griffith (TMSGriffith@aol.com) for more information about this pet.

Reba was dumped on our road around 3/25/07.  She was malnourished, when found.  She has become a very happy and loving dog that would make a great family pet.  She has four white feet and a white neck.

D.O.B.:     ? January 2007

$65 adoption fee will pay for her spay and vaccinations.

pet.name: TG-Rosie
pet.description:
Please contact Tonya Griffith (TMSGriffith@aol.com) for more information about this pet.

(9-28-07) Rosie is a gorgeous Chocolate and White colored Staffordshire and wants to be the sole object of your attention.  She was found as a stray with her puppy.  The people that found her in Arlington had to find her another place since she did not get along with their female Rottweiler mix.  It was probably due to being jealous of attention.

Rosie loves to go for rides, give kisses, and settle in your lap.  If you see her teeth, don't be alarmed because she loves to smile.  She also likes to hunt when outside, so she would probably not be good at a home with cats.  She has done well being paired up with a male as a play mate, but not a female dog for some reason.  She was also being obedience trained by the people that found her, and is also micro chipped.

She has too much energy and gets excited to be around small children - she also starts nipping.  She needs a person that can finish obedience training her, give her the space she needs to run off the energy she has, and stay firm with her when she doesn't follow the rules.  She tends to bolt out a house door when opened, so she needs to be trained to stay inside until given permission to go outside.

She has been adopted 3 times so far, but has not found the right environment for her yet.  Each family has loved her very much, but were not able to deal with her energy.  She can chew through a plastic pet carrier, so a black wire crate would probably work better.  She will need to be crated if left alone.

She is very petite in size, so you wouldn't think she is very strong, but she is stronger than she looks when she is being walked on a leash, so a harness is best when she is walked so she doesn't choke herself.

D.O.B.:     ? 2005
Weight:     39.0 - 7/12/07

$25 adoption fee.  Her original adoption fee has already been paid once.

pet.name: TG-Sarg
pet.breed: Border Collie / Labrador Retriever / Mixed &#40;short coat&#41;
pet.description:
Please contact Tonya Griffith (TMSGriffith@aol.com) for more information about this pet.

Pictures updated 10/26/11.  Sarg loves to run, play, and go in water.  He can dig out of an unsecure fenced perimeter if he wants to or climb a 4 to 5 foot fence.  I recently had to put him in a 5 X 10 kennel while I fixed the height on his dog pen he is in to keep him from climbing out, and he would not go potty in the kennel at all.  He would wait for his potty breaks, so being in a house should not require a lot of extra training even though he has been in a dog pen his entire life.  He does love to give kisses, does very well on a leash, and likes to roam through the woods when he gets out.

D.O.B.:     4/24/04
Weight:    56.3 - 4/20/05
Mother:    Violet
Siblings:   Mick, Mindy Paige, Chief, Captain

$55 adoption fee will pay for his neuter and vaccinations.

pet.name: TG-Suki
pet.breed: Catahoula Leopard Dog / Labrador Retriever / Mixed &#40;short coat&#41;
pet.description:
Please contact Tonya Griffith (TMSGriffith@aol.com) for more information about this pet.

Suki and her brother Kimp were transferred from the shelter around January 25, 2006, due to them not wanting to euthanize them.  Her brother was adopted, but Suki is still waiting for a home.  Suki can climb small fences, so she needs a 6 foot fence to keep her in.  She is very sweet, crate trained, and runs right to her crate when called, so house training would be very easy.  She had mild hip displasia at an early age.  Her leg bone came out of the socket, and was put back in, but wouldn't stay, so she had to have surgery.  The first surgery developed a staff infection, and the ball joint on the leg bone had to be shaved off.  This was an amazing surgery, because her leg muscles hold her leg up now, and she runs around like she has never had surgery.

D.O.B.:     ? November 2005
Weight:     24.0 - 3/14/06; 41.8 9/12/07
Sibling:      Kimp

$60 adoption fee will pay for her spay and vaccinations.

pet.name: Dan
pet.description:
10/9/11 Dan continues to make strides.  He still prefers to be left alone but is starting to let us pet him.  He knows his job is to keep the yard safe from predators like the UPS man and the squirrels.  Of course if anyone came near him he would tuck his tail and run away.  He is crate trained but loves being loss in the house curled up on a dog bed or couch if available.  Dan will need a fenced in yard to make him feel safe.  He promises he will keep the yard safe for you as well.  Dan has been in foster care for several years and deserves to have someone give him a chance. 
 
6/22/11 - Dan is doing better.  He is a handsome dog that is still leery of people.  He will approach humans on his own terms.  He is not trusting of new humans.  He just needs someone to give him a chance and will be a great dog.   He loves being in the house, is housebroken and not a chewer.  He is crate trained and gets along with other dogs.  He will protect your yard from pesky squirrels and other critters that will come near your fence.  If you have room in your heart and patience for earning Dan's trust then he will learn to love you back.  Dan will require a traditional fenced in yard.
 
8/27/10 Dan continues to be leery of humans.  He is doing well in his foster home but prefers t keep his distance from humans.  He will play with all of the dogs and does well. He is looking for a special family that will work with him to feel comfortable with them.
1/19/09 Dan is still looking for a forever home. He is a sweet dog but is still a bit afraid of people but has come a long way. He loves to be in the house with the humans. He will curl up on a dog bed and take the world in as it passes him. He will now come over and give kisses to a human's hand. But he still needs to do things on his time. He will not let you catch him when he is out but will come in when you ask. He would love to a someone who would walk him on a leash then bring him in the house to relax. If outside he works hard as a guard dog. You will know if someone is coming or a squirrel decides to pass by. He says he is just doing his job protecting everyone in the house. His foster home feels safer with him in it. 8/28/08 I am still looking for a home to love me. I am a sweet dog but needs time to learn to trust people. I am great with other dogs. Update 8/18/07 - I am coming out of my shell a little bit. I love being in the house with people. I still love to play with the other dogs as well. My sister Ann and I were wondering through a neighborhood. We were scared. The fleas and ticks covered our body were driving us crazy. A great family with kids were able to coax us into their backyard with food. We were skinny and hunger. They got the fleas and ticks off of us and w were very grateful. I am the more timid one. I am sweet but I am a bit afraid of people. I love other dogs and now feel safe enough to play. I love Ann but will play with others if she is busy. If you adopt me you will need to realize I will need to learn to trust you. I love kids if they are nice to me. I will make a great friend if you dare to take a chance on me.
WE FINALIZE EVERY ADOPTION WITH A HOME VISIT THEREFORE POTENTIAL HOMES MUST BE WITHIN A HOURS DRIVE TIME OF CHARLOTTE NC. A FOSTER PET WILL NOT BE SHIPPED TO SOMEONE LIVING OUTSIDE THE ADOPTION AREA NOR WILL ANYONE BE ALLOWED TO COME PICK A PET UP FROM US. YOU MUST BE 21 TO ADOPT FROM OUR GROUP.

Sincerely,
S.A.F.E. Animal Haven



Please visit our official website at safeanimalhaven.org for more information about our group.

pet.name: AA-Molina
pet.description:
Please contact Tonya Griffith (TMSGriffith@aol.com) for more information about this pet.

Posted 7/21/11 and pictures updated 8/8/11.  This puppy's mother, Paige, was found with the help of her two puppies on 7/20/11.  A neighbor called me 7/19/11 to let me know she saw two puppies in the woods on our road.  I went down the next morning to leave some food, but this puppy was the only one that came to the road.  I pushed through the thicket and greenbriar to make sure the other puppy wasn't injured and found Paige with a 10 foot chain attached to her collar and wrapped around several tree branches, so she couldn't go anywhere.  She had not been there long, but could have died a slow death.  She and her puppies are extremely sweet, and great around my young son, and other dogs.  I have no idea what she would do around cats though.  They all went straight for the water pool when I got them to our property.  I reported them to the Tyler shelter in case someone was looking for them.  The mother appears to be a Pit mix.  They are all leash trained, and we were putting them in a kennel at night and when we ran errands to crate train them, which helps in house training, and they were doing great, even running right in when told to kennel up, but we had to separate them from their mother by putting them in a dog pen when she kept finding ways to escape the perimeter and take them with her for a trip in the woods.  Molina has an underbite, which is common with Boxers and Bullldogs, and she has Shar Pei ears, so she has several breeds mixed in her.

D.O.B.:     ? March 2011
Weight:     24.2 - 7/25/11; 47.4 - 3/3/12

$75 adoption fee will pay for her spay and vaccinations.

pet.name: AA-Alisha
pet.description:
Please contact Tonya Griffith (TMSGriffith@aol.com) for more information about this pet.

Posted 3/7/12, and pictures taken 3/6/12.  Alisha had a litter of four puppies under an elderly man's house, and he didn't know they were there right away.  The puppies were finally lured into his fence with the food dish, and we had to use a live trap to get Alisha on 2/16/12.  She wouldn't come to anyone, but would not leave her puppies.  Once she was trapped, she became a very friendly dog wagging her tail, and wanting to be pet.  She will follow me around wherever I walk, and is leash trained.  I was putting her in a kennel for the first few days here with no mess in between potty breaks, so she may even be house trained.  She does seem somewhat shy of new people, but is fine once she knows that person is ok.  She was able to climb over a very low section of fence one time, but has not done it again, and doesn't appear to be a digger either.

D.O.B.:     ? 2010
Weight:     37.8 - 2/22/12

$86 Adoption fee is exactly what we spent on her spay and vaccinations.

pet.name: Sissy
pet.breed: American Pit Bull Terrier / Mixed &#40;short coat&#41;
pet.description:
SISSY is a young Pit mix who was found as a stray in Cecil Co. The SPCA there will not put Pit Bull up for adoption so her good samaritan rescuer brought her to us rather than have her face certain death. We are not sure if she was neglected or on the run for some time but she came in very thin. We are still getting to know here but this is what her foster Mom says so far:

'Sissy is very sweet, the tail never stops wagging. She will not make eye contact with you, and keeps her head down while you pet her (wagging the whole time). She went right into the crate last night and layed down. She was unsure if she was allowed to come out when the door was open. Shaun left the crate door open all night, but she stayed in it. She's in his room in the basement, and she has full run of the room, but seems to go back to the crate when no one is around. She appears to be housebroken, no accidents and she always goes as soon as we take her out..  She is a little lovebug- just burries her head in your lap & wags her tail.'

She has been spayed, vaccinated, microchipped & tested heartworm neg. Will post more info as we get to know her. Adoption $165. Please fill out an application at www.companimals.org or email for more info.

pet.color: Black with Tan, Yellow or Fawn

Hi my name is Bailey, and I am a 1 1/2yr old Chiweenie.  I am up to date with all my shots, neutered and heart worm negative.  I am partially potty trained, I do very well when someone is home with me, but do not like to be alone so I have boo boos, which I am working very hard to fix.  I do have a couple of old injuries which have healed over and do not bother me at all.  I do have a cataract in my right eye, which was caused by another injury, and has left me blind in that eye.  But that does not seem to bother me either.  I get along well with everyone.  I like playing with my other foster dogs, toys and my foster mom.  I am just a happy little boy!  I love to go for long walks, but do not like the car at all.  I am told that I am just a little sweetheart.  I will give you lots of kisses and at the end of a long hard day will just curl up with you in bed and relax.  If you would like to give me my forever home please go to Abby's Little Friends.com and fill out an application so that we can meet.

pet.name: Buddy

Please contact Pam (pam.alvarez@comcast.net) for more information about this pet.Doxie Mix

pet.name: Winifred Mae
pet.breed: Shih Tzu / Yorkshire Terrier Yorkie / Mixed
pet.description:
MPORTANT; WE ADOPT ONLY IN SOUTH FLORIDA BUT MAKE SOME EXCEPTIONS IN APPROXIMATE AREAS OF Naples, Ft. Myers, Sarasota, Tampa, St. Pete, Lady Lake, The Villages, Orlando, Ormond Beach, Melbourne, etc.

Winifred Mae is the perfect little terrier, extremely intelligent, lovable, bossy with other dogs when necessary yet very popular and playful at the same time. She's a lap dog and begs to be picked up to sit with you, loves to be talked to and to learn new words and games.  Such a sensitive little soul, with so much love to give...with great big serious brown eyes and a stocky little body... anyone who loves terriers will be delighted to meet Winifred Mae.

pet.name: Finley
pet.description: Born in January 2008, Finley, is a female, boxer mix (maybe JRT)..  She does not like cats, but has a very playful personality, knows sit, and likes to be the alpha dog of the household.  Visit our site at http://www.heartwormproject.org/application   and complete an application today!   Our adoption fee is $200.00.

pet.name: Duke
pet.color: Black with Tan, Yellow or Fawn
pet.description:
Please contact Adoption (coastalgsrsd@gmail.com) for more information about this pet.

Hi, my name is Duke. It's too bad that I don’t live in England because I'm sure I would have a family to love and protect and a life style that is befitting my name!  I joined Rescue almost two years ago and because of my good looks, I was quickly adopted.  Unfortunately, the day after I was adopted, my family decided to show me off at this big party with dogs and kids and lots of people.  There was so much going on.  So many people, so much noise, so much commotion.  I was absolutely overwhelmed!  When I am overwhelmed, I am not always on my best behavior.  I'm sorry but I just can't help it.  A few weeks later a nice volunteer took me to her home where I met and got along with other dogs and her daughter.  But again there were so many parties and all these “friends” kept coming over the house.  Yes, I was overwhelmed.  And I thought I had to protect my human mom from all those people who made all that noise.  The next thing I know, I was back in the kennel.  Again.  I am not a puppy.  I am not looking for a wild and crazy home!  I am an adult dog and I am looking for a nice, quiet family who will give me a chance to be the good dog that I know I can be.   I am obedient and quite self confident.  I am house broken and I LOVE riding in the car with my humans.  You can ask any volunteer or dog in the kennel and they will tell you that I am a very nice dog.  All I need is an established family where the humans will respect my space and give me guidance, direction, and mentoring.  I am lucky to be invited to the Coastal swim party almost every Friday. I don’t enjoy swimming as much as some of the other dogs but I do enjoy the bone munching session.  I was told that I am very pleasant company to both dogs and humans when we are there.  So, please check me out!  I might not be a duke in British royalty but I am handsome, affectionate, and loyal.

Please visit http://www.coastalgsrsd.org/ to learn more about our dogs. Click on available dogs to see further descriptions. If you are interested in me, please contact Teresa atbaltao@sbcglobal.net or call (858) 779-9149. Don't forget to fill out our online application.

pet.name: Rah Rah
pet.summary: Once abandoned and now the perfect dog
pet.description:
See Rah Rah's Homepage
Go to our official website

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Please contact Patricia (trisha@pawfirst.com), (580) 491-2337 for more information about this pet.Once abandoned and now the perfect dog

This is Rah Rah. She was living under a pontoon boat during the sweltering summer. She obviously had had recent puppies somewhere but we couldn't find them. It took weeks to gain her trust. She was with a male dog who was very leery of people. When they finally were able to get out of the situation, they were admitted in our vet for avaluation. 
I am not sure how to finish out this story because I am still shocked at what was found after she finally realized that some people are really 'good' and that she had no reason to be afraid. She is currently in foster care along with others and she is such an inspiration to have around. She is the perfect dog. There is a puppy around her and that pup drives her crazy but she doesn't mind at all. This dog is the definition of RESCUE. She was a throwaway. People saw her roaming and just ignored her or, worse.....were cruel to her. Now she is WONDERFUL! She loves life and she loves people. 
She is going to need to go an adopter that is wanting a best friend. She cannot be banished outside. You can tell she wants to be right next to her people all the time. 
She has been promised a wonderful life from this day forward. I do believe she would be the perfect therapy dog candidate.Laid back, calm, and lovable.
She has been spayed, hw negative, dewormed, and current on her vaccinations. She had demodectic mange but it has been treated. She also had lots of worms but ALL GONE.
PLEASE check on any possible pitbull bans in your area before applying. If you are not sure, please mail me Trisha. 
trisha@pawfirst.com
Rah Rah's adoption fee is $125 to help cover some of her vet expenses.
The first step in adopting one of our pets is filling out an adoption application at www.PAWFirst.com
 
After your application is approved, we will schedule an appointment for you to meet the animal you are interested in. Thank you :)

pet.name: Minnie
pet.color: Black with Tan, Yellow or Fawn
pet.description:
Please contact Adoption (coastalgsrsd@gmail.com) for more information about this pet.
There was a great song made popular many years ago with the lyrics, 'I can see clearly now, the rain is gone, I can see all obstacles in my way'. This is Minnie's favorite song today! Minnie had her cataract surgery one week ago and yesterday she had her first follow up visit. We are very happy to tell you that she is recovering from her surgery as we had hoped and expected. The stitches in her eyes have been removed and she definitely is seeing again. She'll have to use the cone for two more weeks but then our diabetic girl will be ready to attend adoption events and look for her forever home. Many thanks to everyone who donated to her medical fund. Your help and support of Rescue made Minnie's surgery possible. We think we can hear her singing more lyrics, 'Gone are the dark clouds that had me blind, It's gonna be a bright, bright sun shiny day!' (Lyrics by Johnny Nash)

pet.name: Artemis
pet.summary: Artemis lost his home when his owner passed away.
pet.color: Black with Tan, Yellow or Fawn
pet.description:
Please contact Adoption (coastalgsrsd@gmail.com) for more information about this pet.Artemis lost his home when his owner passed away.

Artemis joined Rescue many months ago after his human died of cancer and the wife could no longer care for him. He's been living in a foster home so we'd like to tell you about him. In his foster home, there are other dogs and he gets along with everyone. He wants to play and he can be a bit loud, rowdy, and pushy. Of course, in their own way, the other dogs says 'No' and Artemis, in his own way, talks back. Maybe it is how an adolescent dog says, 'Make me!' There are cats in his foster home and he's okay with them. He wants to chase and play but he'll back off when a cat stands up to him. Artemis is good with his basic commands but he does need continuous training and reminders of good doggie manners. He needs a firm but gentle hand and will respond to verbal corrections. He will talk back at times though so the phrase, 'Make me!' does happen from time to time. Artemis will bark at people when they come in the door (unless he is in his crate in which case he'll be quiet). In fact, he does well in a hard crate and his foster mom says he is improving greatly with the wire crate. Did we tell you that he loves Nylabones??
Artemis has epilepsy and experiences grand mal seizures. He currently takes Phenobarbital and other medications may be added as he continues treatment. Treatment does not cure the condition but is aimed to decrease the frequency, severity and duration of the seizures. Artemis may be called a 'special needs' dog but if you are the right family to welcome him into your life, you should know that his foster mom describes him as 'a big love'. Because he has spent time in our kennels as well as the foster home, we should tell you that Artemis has a fan base. One of his weekly dog walkers is a young woman who is currently deployed to serve our country. She regularly sends messages, asking about Artemis, and she is counting the days until her return so she can visit and hug him!

pet.name: Chip
pet.description:
See Chip's Homepage
Go to our official website

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Chip is a very special boy.  He was found wandering around a neighborhood when he was only 8 weeks old.  A vet exam revealed that Chip was both blind and deaf.  It is remarkable that he was walking around alone and was not hurt or killed! 
 
Chip is now 1 year old.  We know that he was born blind and deaf.  He has been diagnosed with Merle Ocular Dysgenesis, a congenital disease which unfortunately has no treatment.
 
Regardless of Chip's 'disabilities' he is a happy, healthy and active dog.  He uses his sense of touch and smell to navigate this world with ease!  He is a true inspiration to us all!
 
Chip is house-trained and leash trained.  He does great with other dogs, but needs to be with dogs who can tolerate his playfulness and inability to notice if they are giving him signals to stop playing.  Chip uses other dogs as his eyes and ears, so he needs another dog in his forever home.  He enjoys being outside and does well with cats and older children.   
 
*FENCED YARD REQUIRED (no underground/invisible fences)
 
If you are interested in adopting Chip, please fill out an application from our website.

pet.name: Bing Bing
pet.description: Born in 2005, Bing Bing is a female Chihuahua mix.  She gets along great with people and other dogs as well as children.  Her foster Mom says she is potty trained, sleeps right up next to you under the covers, runs with the  big dogs ,does not like to be held in your lap but curls right up next to you on the couch. Visit our site at http://www.heartwormproject.org/application   and complete an application today!   Our adoption fee is $200.00.

pet.name: Wynter
pet.description:
See Wynter's Homepage
Go to our official website

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Please contact Patricia (trisha@pawfirst.com), (580) 491-2337 for more information about this pet.
Update: 1/14/13 Wynter is still available for adoption but we found out he is having thyroid issues. They should be able to be treated very cheaply. As of now, he has had some hair loss that is slowly returning. Wynter is my foster dog and he is a wonderful dog. I think he will make a wonderful addition to any family and I don't want him to miss that. If you are willing to work with this kiddo, please let me know :)

Why am I here? I was dumped in front of a school in the middle of a snow storm. How could you?
My foster mom tells me everyday how I am such a good boy. She says all I need is for someone to give me a chance. I am always happy. She makes me smile whenever my name is called. I love it here and I know she will make sure that I get a wonderful home where I will have my very own family. Oh did I mention that I will do just about anything for some neck scratches. They feel sooooo good.
 
How did I get in this situation? Someone dropped me off in front of West Middle School. I played and played with all the kids but when school started, I was left there all alone. That is when I saw a car and a friendly face so I knew that was where I needed to go. It was really really cold outside so this lady started calling me Wynter. She gave me a soft pillow, a warm bed, and even FOOD. I was so hungry that I gulped it all down. I have learned since then that I will never have to worry about my next meal. I have seen little dogs come and go.  I am just waiting for the day when it will be MY turn. Can YOU be my family? I promise to love you always!
 
Wynter's adoption fee is $40 and he is completely updated on all his medical needs. We have had him neutered, given him all his shots, and he is parasite-free. He is also current on his heartworm preventative. He will definitely need to be a primarily indoor dog. He is an amazing house dog. No accidents, not destructive, and content to be laying at your feet whenever you are around.
 
 
Wynter has a nighttime ritual...he always gets up in the bed to get some 'goodnight' love. Then he goes to lay down in his bed.
 
The first step in adopting one of our pets is filling out an adoption application at www.PAWFirst.com
 
After your application is approved, we will schedule an appointment for you to meet the pet.
 
Please understand that we do not ship our pets. You will need to personally come to meet/pickup the pet.

pet.name: Morgan Rose
Poncho

pet.description:
See Poncho's Homepage

A lot of love in a little package

Poncho is a bundle of joy. Sweet once you get to know him but a little cautious in the beginning. Only weighing about 35 pounds, he is medium sized. Kinda like a small shepherd. He LOVES to play ball. If you have a ball, you have a friend for life!

This little guy has been completely vetted. Yep...everything is done. Just waiting for his forever family to find him. His adoption fee is $90.

pet.name: Jersey
pet.color: Black with Tan, Yellow or Fawn
pet.description:
Please contact Adoption (coastalgsrsd@gmail.com) for more information about this pet.

It is very difficult to know what to do and how to act when you suddenly find yourself in a kennel.  There are lots of other dogs whom you don't know, the routine is different from what you were accustomed to, there are lots of people involved in your care, and you don't why you ended up living behind bars.  Jersey is trying very hard to adjust to the new routine so she can feel relaxed and safe but it may take a while.  Loud noises are especially scary.  She's a bit reluctant to be touched, especially in her neck area or on her belly.  But after about twenty minutes of spending time with you, she can roll belly up and have fun.  Likewise, one of our volunteers brushed her for fifteen or more minutes and Jersey was fine.  Suddenly, however, she got up and didn't want the brush anywhere near her.  After sitting for a while, she was again happy to be brushed.  Jersey is very cute and will make a beautiful dog.  Self confidence and trust in the rest of the world - plus receiving lots of love - will go a long way to make Jersey's world a better world for her.  At this point, we think she should be in a home without children.  We don't know how he would be if there were another dog in the family.

June 9, 2012: It's time to tell you where our Jersey Girl spent the most recent Friday afternoon.  She was at The Total Dog in Oceanside.  Actually her story is part of a longer story which we call the 'tale of two tails'.  Jersey lost a large portion of her tail because of what we call “happy tail”.  That's when the tail repeatedly hits concrete or stucco.  The tip breaks open and it is very difficult to heal.  Jersey may not have the big, fluffy tail of most German Shepherd Dogs but she still showed everyone she could swim.  Actually, her pool time started off with an unplanned splash as Coach Carol and Jersey literally flew off the deck and through the air and into the water.  Jersey had been told by many dogs that swimming was great fun so this came as a big surprise. But after a while, she settled down and enjoyed herself.  She’s asked to come back next week.  Of course, the wonderful marrow bone that was waiting for her after her swim session was really nice! 

Please visithttp://www.coastalgsrsd.org/to learn more about our dogs. Click on available dogs to see further descriptions. If you are interested in me, please contact Teresa atbaltao@sbcglobal.net or call (858) 779-9149. Don't forget to fill out our online application.

The minimum adoption donation ranges from $300 to $400. This amount only partially covers the cost of veterinary care, boarding fees, and other miscellaneous expenses involved in the temporary care and adoption of our dogs and is 100% tax deductible.

Prior to placement, all dogs will be spayed or neutered, receive current vaccinations, and are usually microchipped. If not, arrangements will be made on an individual basis. Special consideration may be given to those willing to adopt older dogs or dogs with physical problems.

Our adoption process begins with completing an application on-line. A phone screening will soon follow, and lastly a home visit will be conducted by our volunteers.

We show our dogs at adoption eventsevery weekend! Check our our website to see where we'll be next! Coastal German Shepherd Rescue of Southern California is a non-profit 501(c)3 public charity dedicated to finding loving homes for abandoned German Shepherds. Your tax deductible donations go to support these very deserving animals. Coastal was formed to serve communities in the counties of San Diego, Orange, Los Angeles and the Inland Empire. We are committed to finding loving permanent homes for the orphaned dogs in our care. Coastal is an all volunteer, no-kill, 501 (c) 3 non profit organization.

pet.description:
Please contact Tonya Griffith (TMSGriffith@aol.com) for more information about this pet.

Pictures updated 7/30/10.  Cleo was a stray that wandered up to a house on a county road in Lindale, Texas.  Soon after she appeared, her litter of 10 puppies were born April 9, 2004.  Cleo can jump a 5-6 foot fence unless it is covered on the edge with more fencing to block her jumping.  She loves to hang her head out of a window in a vehicle, loves to run, loves to be around people, and give hugs.  She does not like to be fenced in, but if she is happy where she is, she sticks around if she is not in a fence until you try to drive away somewhere.  If she runs off, she can always be caught by driving a vehicle after her and opening the door, since she loves going for rides, she will jump right in.

pet.description:

pet.name: Aisin
pet.breed: Irish Setter / Chocolate Labrador Retriever &#40;medium coat&#41;
pet.description: Aisin was a feral (wild) dog living outside a factory in London, Kentucky. Born in the wild, she had no social interaction with humans. Factory workers left food scraps outside for her until the factory owners decided to have her shot. A local animal rescue organization, Homeward Bound Canine Rescue and Rehabilitation, trapped her to save her from being killed. Aisin arrived at the rescue frightened, unsocialized and missing much of her fur from mange. She was scared of the kennel environment and was transferred to World Animal Foundation for rehabilitation. Aisin arrived terrified of humans and hid under a bed for several days, refusing to eat or even move. She trembled and defecated if anyone came close to her. After several days she began to come out of hiding for food and water at night when no one was around. After several weeks she slowly began to take treats from humans. After a month she gained the courage to go outside during the day and slowly began interacting with other dogs. Aisin is now house broken, plays with other dogs and follows humans around. She begs for treats and now plays with toys. She will let her caretakers touch her, but is still shy and cautious. She is terrified of a leash but volunteers are slowly working to leash train her. She needs a patient family willing to continue to work with her. Whoever adopts her will need to understand that she'll probably start off shy and timid. She's very gentle, likes other dogs and does well with cats. Aisin is about 5 years old, spayed, wormed, current on vaccines and microchipped. Her hair is almost all grown back in and is now soft and shiny. Aisin is a special dog who deserves to live. She is very low maintenance and will require a fenced yard and other dogs to interact with. Her adoption fee is $150.00. If you are interested, please contact Homeward Bound at 859-490-0486 or e-mail homewardbound1818@yahoo.com.

pet.description: MPORTANT; WE ADOPT ONLY IN SOUTH FLORIDA BUT MAKE SOME EXCEPTIONS IN APPROXIMATE AREAS OF Naples, Ft. pet.name: AA-Amber
pet.description:
Please contact Tonya Griffith (TMSGriffith@aol.com) for more information about this pet.

Pictures taken 12/29/10.  Amber was dumped on a county road.  She was afraid to come up to anyone keeping her tail tucked under.  Once she was trapped, and had a leash put on her, she became a very happy loveable young dog.  She started to jump 5 feet high to kiss my face.  I put her in a dog pen with other dogs, and she tried licking their faces as well.  She would probably not be good around really small children due to the jumping up, but she could probably be trained to do some tricks with that ability.  She is a beautiful Light Brown Brindle with White, and her eyes match her fur.  We pulled her out of her dog pen November 2011, and are crating her with no problems, and she keeps trying to come inside our home, so she is house trained.  She also may like to ride in a vehicle, since she loves to jump in my truck.

D.O.B.:     ? 1 year old 12/29/10
Weight:     35.8 - 12/29/10

$85 adoption fee will pay for her spay and vaccinations.

pet.name: Grace
pet.description:
See Grace's Homepage
Go to our official website

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Grace was picked up as a small puppy by a good Samaritan when she wandered onto a city gas station parking lot. She was adopted out, but unfortunately, Grace's adopter could not keep her due to her work schedule.  She was adopted out again, but poor Grace was once again returned - after SIX YEARS - due to a change in her owner's living situation.

Grace is good natured, and fun, fun, fun. She has lived with a cat, and she's good with most dogs, but she loves people most of all.  Grace will make a wonderful pet, but she does need an owner who understands that dogs need to know who's in charge - she's quite clever and quickly figures out who will let her be boss - and that dogs love stability and do best with consistency.

pet.name: AA-Baker
pet.breed: Staffordshire Bull Terrier / Boxer / Mixed &#40;short coat&#41;
pet.description:
Please contact Tonya Griffith (TMSGriffith@aol.com) for more information about this pet.

Posted 7/21/11 and pictures updated 1/22/13.  This puppy's mother, Paige, was found with the help of her two puppies on 7/20/11.  A neighbor called me 7/19/11 to let me know she saw two puppies in the woods on our road.  I went down the next morning to leave some food, but only one puppy came to the road.  I pushed through the thicket and greenbriar to make sure this puppy wasn't injured and found Paige with a 10 foot chain attached to her collar and wrapped around several tree branches, so she couldn't go anywhere.  She had not been there long, but could have died a slow death.  She and her puppies are very sweet, and great around my young son, and other dogs.  I have no idea what he would do around cats though.  They all went straight for the water pool when I got them to our property.  I reported them to the Tyler shelter in case someone is looking for them.  The mother appears to be a Pit mix, and the puppies appear to look like a Staffordshire mix, but we are unsure as to what they are really mixed with.  We were putting them in a kennel at night and when we ran errands to crate train them, which helps in house training, and they were doing great, even running right in when told to kennel up, but we had to separate them from their mother by putting them in a dog pen when she kept finding ways to escape the perimeter and take them with her.  Baker is extremely sweet, and would be a great family dog.  He has a submissive personality to the other dogs.  He will also need to have another dog to be with, since he doesn't like to be alone, and he also plays fetch with toys or balls non-stop.

D.O.B.:     ? March 2011
Weight:     26.6 - 7/25/11; about 50 pounds now

$80 adoption fee will pay for his neuter and vaccinations.

Harley is a male Corgi/shephed mix, light tan, cream color. Somewhat fluffy, shorter like a Corgi but looks more like a shepherd. About 18 inches tall and 40 pounds. He was last seen in his apartment at 20th and Connecticut. He was wearing an orange Harley Davidson Collar. He is microchipped and registered to Friends for Life in Gilbert, Arizona. All the animals in his apartment building were smal.ler then he is and were found alive. He is very friendly, loves people and loves children.

pet.description:
RESCUED AFTER WEEKS OF RUNNING SCARED AND STARVING ON THE STREETS. CHESTER is a sweet and loving five pound little chi and is, the vet thinks, around seven years old. He is  very calm and sweet. He loves all people and other dogs and would  be greet in a home with another small dog or dogs.

Chester is neutered ,microchipped and current on shots.

pet.name: Spike
pet.description:
I'm Spike.  I'm a male Chihuahua mix.  I was born around November, 2010.  I'm an absolute cutie.  My current humans are having to find a new home for me due to an illness in their family.  I don't want to lose them but they say it's best for me to have a new home that can give me the attention and love that I deserve.  I'm very active and would need a fenced in yard to keep me safe as I play with my new family.  I love to run.  I'm neutered, up to date on my shots, and micro chipped.  If you're interested in being my forever family, please call PAWS at 256-383-0690 or visit the website at www.shoalspaws.com to complete an application.



To adopt this wonderful pet, complete our online application at: http://shoalspaws.com/adoption/adoption-application/ Once we receive your application, our adoption counselor will review it and contact you as soon as possible. Our adoption fees are: $100.00 for mixed breed puppies/dogs and $175.00 for purebred puppies/dogs; $75 for cats.

pet.name: Jessie
pet.description:
Jessie was wandering the streets when a kind animal lover discovered her. No tags, collar or any method of identifying her owner was found. GSROC could not bear the thought of this beautiful girl alone and on her own.

 

She is approximately 3 years old and has a quiet nature. She is quiet and somewhat unsure around strangers right now. Jessie is not sure exactly what has happened to her and she is uncertain.

Recently we introduced Jessie to some cats. She let us know in no uncertain terms that she is not a fan of felines! Due to her reaction, we believe she would do best in a home with no small dogs or cats.

We are just getting to know Jessie and will update her profile shortly.



Please go to our website and complete an adoption application at: http://www.gsroc.org/application.asp. An adoption counselor will contact you to go over your application and assist you in determining which dog may be best for your particular situation.

pet.name: zzz - Molly
pet.description:
Molly is spayed, she is good around people not sure about kids she is always around adults. Wants to play all the time somewhat high energy when she does get out of the side yard, but if she had a full yard to play in all day then she would be happy.  Molly would prefer to be the only dog and would love to have all your attention. She gives lots of love and likes to go on walks. She also likes to cuddle.

Please contact Marianne Jones 714-983-2410, purplesky53@aol.com

pet.name: zzz - Dane
pet.description:
Hi my name is Dane.  I am a 2 year old neutered pit bull mix.  I am very sweet and I would love to find a family that can give me the attention I deserves. I am up to date on my shots and walk nicely on a leash.  I have not been around a lot of children or cats.  I used to live with a small dog in my other home but I did not like sharing my food with him.  I love to sit on your lap and cuddle because I love people.  I am potty trained as well.

Please contact Holle Dyonisio if you are interested in meeting me - hdyonisio@aol.com

pet.name: zzz - Harley
pet.description:
Harley is four years old, very calm and gentle and amazing around kids. My nephew tugs on his ears, pets his head to hard and he just lays there and allows it. He's good on or off a leash, comes when he's called he's awesome. He's potty trained, no health problems, good around other dogs and he also likes to sun bathe.

Please contact Heather if you are interested in Harley heathersnooks12@gmail.com

pet.name: Arlo
pet.description:
Arlo is a darling little fella.... he came to us from a shelter where they knew the chances of him getting adopted were slim, as he's blind.  That seems to be a big roadblock in our human minds,, but somebody forgot to tell the dogs!!  This little guy gets around amazingly well, and has right from the get-go.  While in quarantine when he first arrived, we did leash walks and he just pranced around happy as could be.  When he was introduced to the other dogs, it took him no time at all to figure out the doggie door and even the ramp up and down into the yard from the deck.

He's claimed his favorite spot on the couch which he accesses by way of a ramp, and he figured that out all by himself too.  He'll happily snuggle up for cuddle time, but if you're busy, he'll just curl up in a doggie bed and take a nap. 

Between his attitude and his shorter haircoat, he's very low maintainance and will make someone a very loving companion.

pet.name: zzz - Skipper
pet.description:
Skipper is a male sheperd mixed that was found on the streets with wounds all over his neck.  His wounds have healed now and he is an active happy boy looking for a home or rescue.  He is neutered, microchiped, and up to date on shots.  He is good with people and dogs.

Please contact animalrescuehelper@gmail.com for more information.

pet.name: A-Lucy
pet.description:
Please contact Tonya Griffith (TMSGriffith@aol.com) for more information about this pet.

Robert Bozick
Lindale, TX
903/882-3825
bozick@earthlink.net

Posted 6/17/13.  I found Lucy around April 2013 starving, and had two pups.  I found homes for the two puppies, and now need to find a home for Lucy.  She has been outside, and doing great, but she was afraid to come near me at first, probably due to being on her own for awhile.  I earned her trust, and she is doing great now.  I don't know if she had been house trained before I found her.  She needs a home that will allow her to use up the energy she has, and will make someone a very good dog.  She still has very White teeth, so she is still a young dog, and a vet clinic will be able to give a better estimate of her age by looking at her teeth.

Anyone wanting to adopt her, must be able to have her spay and vaccinations done, if not done already.  There are several low cost spay/neuter locations on the home page of this web site if needed.

pet.name: zzz - Chandler
pet.description:
Meet Chandler. He is a seven year old Chihuahua who is a very sweet and loving dog. He loves to cuddle and is a pretty mellow dog. He mostly just hangs out all day and is wonderful with people and very good with kids. He would prefer to be the only dog but with a proper introduction, he should be fine with a brother or sister to play with.  He has no health issues or medications.  He is fixed and walks well on a leash. He is potty trained but as with most little dogs, he will have an accident if left inside too long. At our house he is trained to go to the bathroom in a specific area in our yard. He is a sweet heart with people and wants to cuddle in blankets all the time.

Please contact Jaclyn jaclynfowle@yahoo.com if you are interested in meeting Chandler

pet.name: Courtesy Listing: Roscoe
pet.description:
See Courtesy Listing: Roscoe's Homepage
Go to our official website

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Roscoe is great with other dogs and cats, good with kids but very bouncy so he would probably do best with older kids or adults. He is crate trained, rides great in the car, loves to run on the treadmill, and is a soft and sensitive guy. Please conact Jen at aneducateddog@yahoo.com or 760.519.8652.

pet.name: Courtesy Listing: Marco
pet.description:
See Courtesy Listing: Marco's Homepage

Marco is 3.5 years old and very friendly.

pet.name: zzz - Emily
pet.description:
Meet Emily!  She is a beautiful and very human and child friendly dog we adopted 4 years ago when she was approximately 6 months old. We have another dog a year older, a cat and a turtle who she gets along with well. She loves to run, play fetch, chase bubbles, wade in her kiddie pool, and get lots of belly rubs. She would be best being the only dog or have a proper introduction to other dogs.  She is such a happy dog , but we are not the best family for her right now.  She weighs about 50 pounds, fixed, and up to date on shots.

Please contact Charlene if you would like to meet Emily cpt37@yahoo.com

pet.name: Chocolatte
pet.description:
Chocolatte (aka Choco ) is a 2.5 year old chocolate lab mix. He, his sister Lissy and his mom Nanny Duck were found in a junk yard, starving and scared. Now,  Choco is a big lovebug! He is a big guy and is very active. He loves to play and does well with most other dogs, even little dogs. After a day of playing, he loves to snuggle on the couch with his people. He has passed a basic obedience class and loved it, and would do well in continuing classes. He  would prefer a home without little children, because he doesn't know how big he is.  Choco is neutered and up to date on vaccinations.

All the adoptable AARF dogs are in foster homes to get them ready for their forever homes. If you are interested in meeting one of our adorable pooches, please fill out our adoption application and we'll get back to you with any questions. Then we can schedule a time for the two of you to meet!

pet.name: Miss Lissy
pet.description:
Miss Lissy is a 2.5 year old black lab mix. She and her mom and  brother were found in a junk yard, starving and scared. Now, Lissy is  a happy and healthy girl! She can be a little bit shy with new folks,  but is very friendly when she knows her people. She does well with  other dogs and has some basic obedience training. She has been spayed,  has all of her vaccinations and has completed a basic obedience class.

 

All the adoptable AARF dogs are in foster homes to get them ready for their forever homes. If you are interested in meeting one of our adorable pooches, please fill out our adoption application and we'll get back to you with any questions. Then we can schedule a time for the two of you to meet!

pet.name: Nanny Duck
pet.breed: American Pit Bull Terrier / Labrador Retriever / Mixed &#40;short coat&#41;
pet.description:
Nanny Ducky is Miss Lissy and Choco's mom. She and her pups were found in a junkyard, and she was such a good mom! She keep them safe in a very dangerous environment, and now it's her turn for a forever home. Ducky is about 4 years old, and is spayed, up to date on her vaccinations, crate trained and has completed a basic obedience class. Nanny Ducky gets along with most dogs, but can be a little protective (not surprising, given her history.) She would probably prefer a home without cats. She is a happy, happy girl, and would love to have   couch to snuggle on, some green grass to roll in and a forever home where she will always feel safe.

All the adoptable AARF dogs are in foster homes to get them ready for their forever homes. If you are interested in meeting one of our adorable pooches, please fill out our adoption application and we'll get back to you with any questions. Then we can schedule a time for the two of you to meet!

pet.name: Vyse
pet.description:
Please contact Violet (drawsdogs@gmail.com) for more information about this pet.

All dogs are spayed/neutered prior to adoption. They are also microchipped, fully vaccinated and treated for parasites. Adoption fees vary from 50$ to 350$. Application and home check required prior to adoption.



Vyse is a handsome, 3 year old Pit Bull. He is a realy nice, well behaved boy. An easy keeper. Would be best as an only pet but would love a family with kids. He is the perfect companion for an active family who likes movie nights in front of the tv. He is housebroken, crate trained, leash trained and knows basic commands. And the icing on the cake is his unique and beautiful coloring. He does have some minor skin issues that are being sorted out. But is otherwise a healthy boy. Adoption fee $150.

pet.name: Foster/Volunteer
pet.description:
We are looking for foster homes across California and Oregon that have a love for Boxers. Whether you are willing to foster over night or extended amount of time for this loveable breed please let us know. We can't do it without you!!!

Volunteers are needed to for transporting! If you can't foster but want to help us out, please let us know as well!
 
Please fill out our foster application here: http://www.jotform.us/wcbr/app

Please "Like" our Facebook page and follow us at www.facebook.com/WestCoastBoxerRescue.


If you are interested in this dog, please read our adoption process and fill out an adoption application here: http://www.westcoastboxerrescue.org/adopt/.

Due to the volume of inquires we receive, we are unable to reply to inquiries without adoption application.

Please follow us on our Facebook page: http://www.facebook.com/WestCoastBoxerRescue.

pet.description:
Freddy is a six year old, seven pound toy poodle who lost his home.  He is great with other dogs, housebroken, fixed, chipped and very loving, but takes time to bond.  No kids as he can get protective.  Call 310-285-3221

immanuel222@att.net

pet.name: Misty
pet.description: Misty is a 13 month-old adora-a-bull. She is housetrained, crate trained, is dog and cat social, and just wants to please her people! For Misty, there is nothing better in the world than sitting next to her person and receiving pets and kisses! She is looking for her furever home. If you're interested in Misty, please go to www.dontbullymerescuetexas.org/adopt and fill out an adoption application

pet.name: Daphne
pet.description: Tranferred to the Stellas Account. No longer ZAR animal. Daphne has been in foster care for around four years. She is still shy and does not like most men. She does fine with women, once she gets to know them. She can be scared very easily, and so needs quiet home with no children.

pet.name: Maris
pet.description:
Transferred to the Stellas Account. No longer a Zoi's Animal.

I was born without a pancreas. I need special enzymes put on my food in order to absorb proteins. This is very costly. I am very affectionate to people. I don't like all dogs but some are ok. I get to live my days out at Zoi's, but I do need help with my monthly meds.

As of 03/2009, Maris is 7 years old.

pet.name: Lilly
pet.breed: American Pit Bull Terrier / Pointer / Mixed &#40;short coat&#41;
pet.description:
Please contact Cherie (cherie@mistyeyes.org) for more information about this pet.

Meet Lilly. Lilly was picked up by animal control as a stray. She was adopted from animal control and they just loved her but a neighbor said 'Oh my goodness, that's a pit bull!!' and the family brought her back. REALLY!!! Lilly is just the sweetest dog you can ever meet. She is good with other dogs, absolutely loves, loves, loves, kids and is a great dog. Please consider adopting Lilly into your family. Don't let the 'bad rap' prevent this awesome girl from getting the family she so deserves!!



All of our pets are current on vaccinations. Dogs are heartworm tested. Kitties are FIV/FeLV tested. All are spayed/neutered, on flea, tick and heartworm prevention and micro chipped. Our adoption fee for dogs is $180.00. Our adoption fee for cats is $100.00 and if you adopt a second cat at the same time the adoption fee will only be $150.00 total.

Zoe is a young female catahoula, pit bull mix. Zoe is high energy and loves to play Fetch, she also loves to train, which will need to be maintained once she finds a home of her own. Zoe is looking for her perfect home, which will be one with a yard, and no other pets, and a family who has breed experience. Any children in Zoe's new family should be over 10 years old.

pet.description:

Pictures updated 12/18/12.  Wilbur was transferred from the shelter February 7, 2006, due to them not wanting to euthanize him and his brother.  He is very affectionate, has a lot of playful energy, and he can jump over a four foot fence, so he will need a 6 foot fenced yard.  He is also very intelligent, in that he will drag a dog house next to the fence and use it to jump over the fence.  He seems to have settled down at our location, and doesn't try to escape as long as he is a yard dog, and not put in a dog pen.  He is also crate and house trained.  He still likes to chew on things, so chew toys and real bones are a must.

D.O.B.:     ? November 2005
Weight:      25.9 - 2/22/06; 69.6 - 4/30/08
Sibling:      Orville

$55 adoption fee will pay for his neuter and vaccinations.

pet.name: Princess
pet.description: PRINCESS was dumped at a high kill shelter in NYC when her owners moved overseas. She is a really good, loyal dog. At 5-7 yrs old, she is well past the puppy stage - yet still an active girl. Princess LOVES toys - kongs, tennis balls, you name it! Gets along with other dogs - but doesn't like to share her toys. LOVES the great outdoors & hikes & especially STICKS! Would do best in a home with older kids, a laid back other dog or fine as an only dog as well. Prefers a 'cat free' home. Princess has been spayed, vaccinated, heartworm neg and microchipped. Adoption $165

pet.name: BRUNO
Zeus
pet.description:
Zeus has spent his short life alone, unloved and kept in a yard by himself. His basic needs of food and water were met, but he never got to experience the outside world. No trips to the park, no car rides, little if any affection. His world consisted of his yard and seeing his people.

 

His family decided they no longer wanted him and asked GSROC for help. When we learned of plight, we rushed to help him.

Zeus is now slowly learning about the outside world. Although he is obedience trained, his trainer has worked with him and he is slowly learning that humans can be friendly and fun. He is very cautious of strangers and you must earn his trust before he relaxes.

His trainer reports that once his trust is earned, he relaxes and is a love bug! Zeus walks well on a leash and follows commands.

Based on his history, we recommend Zeus be placed in an adult home with an experienced GSD owner. This boy has lots of love to give, all he needs is the right human.

If you are interested in meeting Zeus, please complete the online application and an adoption counselor will contact you.

 



Please go to our website and complete an adoption application at: http://www.gsroc.org/application.asp. An adoption counselor will contact you to go over your application and assist you in determining which dog may be best for your particular situation.

pet.name: Keola
FOSTERS NEEDED
pet.description:
See FOSTERS NEEDED's Homepage
Go to our official website

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

 
 
PLEASE NOTE: GPMR communicates primarily by email.  If you have any questions regarding one of our Mastiffs, please read their bio and if you still have questions- drop us an email at info@greatplainsmastiffrescue.org .  If you have questions about our adoption procedures, please go to our Pages of Interest on the left hand column under 'Adoption Info.'  We answer email inquiries almost immediately-usually always within a few hours and phone calls are returned with 24-36 hours. 
 
GPMR does not have a shelter. All of our dogs are kept in loving foster homes. We must have a completed adoption
application on file before meeting any of our mastiffs.
  
GPMR adopts to the states of Oklahoma, Texas, Kansas, Arkansas, Missouri, Louisiana and parts of Colorado. 
!!!Any mastiffs being adopted out of the state of Oklahoma require a health certificate to be paid for by the adopter!!!
 

 

 


Need Volunteers for Fostering:

GPMR does not have a shelter or facility where we can house Mastiffs when they come into rescue. We are able to take Mastiffs into rescue because of our caring volunteers who foster those Mastiffs until they can find their forever home.

IF YOU CAN HELP FOSTER, OR VOLUNTEER IN ANY WAY, PLEASE FILL OUT OUR ONLINE VOLUNTEER AND/OR FOSTER FORM. WE NEED DEDICATED VOLUNTEERS SO WE CAN HELP MORE MASTIFFS IN NEED.

THANK YOU!

Note: the dog pictured is a previously adopted dog - please go to   http://www.greatplainsmastiffrescue.org/animals/list?Status=Available
for the current list of dogs, and there are always dogs waiting to come into the rescue when we have a foster home available - please consider fostering tday!



Save a Mastiff...Adopt, Foster, Volunteer!

pet.name: A-Sadie
pet.description:
Please contact Tonya Griffith (TMSGriffith@aol.com) for more information about this pet.

For adoption information, please contact:
Rita
Carthage, TX
903/522-1005
rlmiddlegate79@gmail.com

Posted 7/3/12, and pictures updated 10/21/13.  Sadie came to our fence about a month ago from 7/3/12.  I told her to go away, but found her in our yard the next day keeping very good company with one of our dogs who dislikes all other dogs.  She visited all our dogs, and they all liked her, even one who will not let anyone or any other animal near his food bowl will let Sadie eat with him.  We took her to our vet, she was put on heartworm prevention, spayed, vaccinated, treated for fleas, a pill for tapeworms, weighs just under 40 pounds, and is around 8 months old when posted 7/3/12.

Sadie is loving, active, has had a lot of obedience training now, is very smart, learns quickly, knows heel, sit, down, and stay.  She loves to eat, spend time on the couch in the house with her person(s), loves to chase birds or any other critter out of her yard, loves to run, and loves when anyone comes to visit her.  She is not bad about jumpig up on people, but does need a secure fenced yard at least 5 feet high, and secured at the bottom.

We cannot keep her, and need to find a home for her as soon as possible.  Anyone interested in adopting her must be willing to be thoroughly interviewed....and open....to a home visit.  There will be a nominal adoption fee - just because anyone interested in Sadie must know and be willing to commit to certain expenses connected with owning a dog.

Posted 10/24/13.  Hank was 6 days away from being euthanized in Carthage, so we took him in.  He is about 2 years old when posted 10/24/13, has a wonderful temperament, loving, affectionate, good with people and animals in house and out.  He is now looking for a forever home, where he can get much more attention than he gets with us.  He is not in our house much, but has not tried to urinate when inside.  He weighs about 55 pounds, and will need a securely fenced yard.

Anyone interested in adopting him must be willing to be thoroughly interviewed....and open....to a home visit.  There will be a nominal adoption fee - just because anyone interested in Hank must know and be willing to commit to certain expenses connected with owning a dog.

pet.name: zzz - Mina
pet.description: Meet Mina!  She is a one and half year old (10/2013) American Pit Bull Terrier mix.  She has a beautiful spotted colored coat that makes us wonder what other breed she is mixed with.   She is fixed and up to date on her shots.  Mina would prefer to be the only dog so that she can have all the attention on her.  She is great with adults and kids once she get over her initial shyness.  She is very quick to warm up and would love to be a part our your family.  She walks very nicely on leash and is smart so can be easily trained with some time.  She is an inside/outside dog but really enjoys sitting outside and sunbathing.  Mina is located in Lakewood, CA and needs a new home as soon as possible.  Please contact - Emily Jimenez at (562) 441-9018 if you would like to meet Mina.

pet.name: Spot
pet.description:
See Spot's Homepage
Go to our official website

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Meet Spot...a girl looking for her forever home.Yes, I know Spot is not a very girly name and she will accept a name change. I am her foster mom though and the name Spot works here :) 

Spot is a pretty girl who was saved from out local animal control the day that her time was up. We actually went in to pull another dog that day but she was just sitting there so nicely. She had to be saved. 

Spot is a very sweet girl. VERY. She will gently nudge you for attention. She needs to be an indoor dog. She would not be happy outside and there is no reason to keep her outside anyways since she is kennel trained. She wants her family there with her all the time. If you sit somewhere, she will sit next to you. If you walk to the next room, odds are that she will not be far behind you. She gets along wonderfully with children. She also gets along with almost all other dogs in her foster home (too many to mention haha). She will answer any challenges though from a couple dominant females in her home so that should be taken into consideration be any potential adopters. If you have a very dominant female, she may not be the best candidate for your new family. Other than that, not too many flags. 

A privacy fence would be ideal because she could definitely get over a chain link fence if she wanted.

Spot is current on her vetting. She is completely vaccinated, dewormed, heartworm tested (negative) and spayed.

Spot's adoption fee is $100.
